  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are currently positioned in a PIN regime with spot at 6560 sitting between the massive negative gamma wall at 6550 (-22.4B) and the flip point at 6584, creating a stabilizing environment where dealers will mechanically buy any dip toward 6550 and sell strength into the 6575-6580 gamma wall (+31.7B). The recent GEX surge indicates fresh options flow has amplified dealer hedging obligations, making the 6550-6580 range even stickier with mean-reverting behavior expected. Watch for aggressive dealer buying if we test 6550 and systematic selling pressure into any rally toward the 6580 max positive gamma strike.",
